Cypriot Bank Deposits Increase 3% in April, Central Bank Reports

-- B y   S t e l i o s   O r p h a n i d e s
-- 
2011-05-27T13:01:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/cypriot-bank-deposits-increase-3-in-april-central-bank-reports.html
Cypriot banking deposits rose 3
percent in April from the previous month, the  Central Bank of
Cyprus  said.  Deposits rose to 70.8 billion euros ($100.8 billion)
representing an annual 14 percent increase, the central bank
said in a  statement  on its website today.  Non-euro deposits, mainly in dollars, increased by 1.5
billion euros. Deposits in euros climbed by 550.7 million euros.  Lending rose at an annual rate of 9.6 percent to 63.3
billion euros, mainly on a 25 percent increase in loans to other
financial intermediaries to 7.6 billion euros and an 11 percent
rise in mortgages to 14.5 billion euros, the bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stelios Orphanides in Nicosia at  sorphanides@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  